<font color="#FF0000">SPECIAL TRAINING</font><br>
<tt>Sat Sep 27 15:04:48 US/Eastern 1997
</tt><p>
John, <br>
Parachutes and Life Preservers? That's why I wanted to join the Army, or the Air Force they gave you special equipment to jump out of planes with. <br><br>
No, I wasn't special anything, But I do like all those Special bumper stickers. I just happened to be at the right place at the right time or perhaps the wrong place at the right time. <br><br>
Our platoon was sparrowhawked in a few times to get Force Recon Marines out from where they had suffered great casualties, it wasn't pretty. <br>
 <br>
Other then Machine Gun school I had no other special training, Sgt. Nelson often told us,&quot; You won't die if they shoot you only 3 or 4 times. Unless they shoot you in the head or chest you won't die and if you get killed you better keep fighting, Marine you will not die without getting the bastard that killed you.&quot;<br><br>
Then again I remember once, when we were ambushed out in an open rice paddy field. I'm thinking as I'm hitting the deck, &quot;Stimulus response, that what my history teacher told us about what Einstein said. Stimulus response, they shoot and we hit the deck. <br>
I think we were conditioned as SW has mentioned by many.<br>
 Just think about the ones you helped survive because of what you learned and shared with others.<br><br>
Knowing that has been a great comfort to me. As far as I know after I left the squad I had been in charge of in Nam, only one Marine did not make it back. A female gook walked right up to him after he had helped a family get across a flooded creek bed and pulled the pin on a grenade killing them both.
